msgstr "window order by time of last use"

#. type: defun
#: original_texis/windows.texi:1862
#, no-wrap
msgid "window-use-time &optional window"
msgstr "window-use-time &optional window"

#. type: defun
#: original_texis/windows.texi:1865
msgid "This functions returns the use time of window @var{window}.  @var{window} must be a live window and defaults to the selected one."
msgstr "この関数はウィンドウ@var{window}の使用回数をリターンする。@var{window}は生きたウィンドウでなければならずデフォルトは選択されたウィンドウ。"

#. type: defun
#: original_texis/windows.texi:1872
msgid "The @dfn{use time} of a window is not really a time value, but an integer that does increase monotonically with each call of @code{select-window} with a @code{nil} @var{norecord} argument.  The window with the lowest use time is usually called the least recently used window while the window with the highest use time is called the most recently used one (@pxref{Cyclic Window Ordering})."
msgstr "ウィンドウの@dfn{使用回数(use time)}は実際にはtime値ではなく、@code{nil}の@var{norecord}引数による@code{select-window}の呼び出しごとに毎回単調に増加する整数。通常は最小の使用回数をもつウィンドウはもっとも最近使用されていないウィンドウ(the least recently used window)、最大の使用回数をもつウィンドウはもっとも最近使用されたウィンドウ(the most recently used window)と呼ばれる(@ref{Cyclic Window Ordering}を参照)。"

#. type: section
#: original_texis/windows.texi:1876
#, no-wrap
msgid "Cyclic Ordering of Windows"
msgstr "Cyclic Ordering of Windows"

#. type: cindex
#: original_texis/windows.texi:1877
#, no-wrap
msgid "cyclic ordering of windows"
msgstr "cyclic ordering of windows"

